    "attributes": {
        "action": "Stop charging for Vehicle Excise Duty",
        "additional_details": "Every year \u00a3100 million worth of VED goes unpaid through evasion.\r\nCar insurance and MOT details are now held on a central register so the outdated requirement to provide these documents when taxing a car is un-necesaary. \r\nVED could be collected by adding a fraction of a pence to every litre of fuel sold, this would create a simple and unavoidable way of collecting the revenue. It would also encourage people to buy fuel efficient cars therefore helping the environment.",
        "background": "The government wastes taxpayer money by collecting vehicle excise duty in the form of a tax on the car.\r\nInstead the revenue currently generated through VED could be collected by adding a fraction of a pence to every litre of fuel sold.",
